		<header>
			
			<h1>Exponential growth in UHT milk demand foreseen in Africa</h1>

			
			<h4>
												02 February 2014
										</h4>

					</header>


		
		
					<p>According to packaging manufacturer SIG Combibloc, demand for long-life milk in Africa is set to “grow exponentially”. Developments in South Africa are taken as indicative of a wider trend; according to the Milk Producers Association (MPA) of South Africa, demand for UHT milk is growing at 8.3% while the market for pasteurised milk is declining at around 6.5% per annum.</p><p>In Africa and the Middle East, demand for packaging used in UHT production “has witnessed growth rates of up to 35% per year” since 2001. Milk and milk product markets are most strongly established in Southern and Eastern Africa. In West Africa, however, “the majority of white milk is sold in powdered format” while “other dairy products like fermented milk, flavoured milk and drinking yoghurt are hugely popular.”</p><p>Press reports note an established demand for “long-life milk powder in small sachets” in West Africa. One Nigerian state governor observed that 95% of all milk consumed in Nigeria is now imported, and other reports noted that Nigeria “supplies neighbouring countries, including Benin, Niger, Chad and the Central African Republic”.</p><p>But, according to the major West African dried milk-powder distributor Promasidor, “milk powder doesn’t work in Kenya [because] there is a very large dairy industry.”</p><p>Between January and August 2013, at the global level, EU skimmed milk-powder (SMP) exports were overtaken by US SMP exports. The growth in EU SMP exports, which has taken place since 2008, now appears to have peaked, with monthly sales throughout 2013 below 2012 levels. By August 2013, cumulative EU SMP exports were 31% below the level attained during the corresponding period in 2012.</p><p><b>EU SMP and cheese exports 2007–2012 (tonnes)</b></p><table class="renderedtable" border="1" cellpadding="2" cellspacing="0">
<tr>
<td width="110" valign="top">  &nbsp;
  </td><td width="110" valign="top">  2007
  </td><td width="110" valign="top">  2008
  </td><td width="110" valign="top">  2009
  </td><td width="110" valign="top">  2010
  </td><td width="110" valign="top">  2011
  </td><td width="110" valign="top">  2012
  </td>
</tr>

