</table>
<p>Source: EC, ‘Milk market situation’, 5 November 2013</p><p>EU SMP prices since April 2013 have been substantially above the price levels prevailing since 2010, and EU monthly exports of cheese have been above the 2012 level, suggesting that the trend of increasing cheese exports is likely to have continued into 2013.</p><p>The main markets for EU SMP are China and Mexico. The Danish company Arla announced in December 2013 that it would be expanding its trading activities in SMP through Fonterra’s GlobalDairyTrade auction. This decision was taken as a result of the continued pressure on European markets and the potential for higher returns on Asian markets.</p>
		
		
